perty) (Tyne and Wear) Order 1987|publisher=Legislation.gov.uk|accessdate=15 September 2019}}</ref> The county council was based at [[Sandyford House]] in [[Newcastle upon Tyne]]. It was replaced with five authorities: [[Metropolitan Borough of Gateshead]], [[Newcastle City Council]], [[North Tyneside Council]], [[South Tyneside Council]] and [[Sunderland City Council]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twmuseums.org.uk/files/5578-acquisitions-and-disposal-policy-archives.pdf|title=Archives Collection, Acquisition and Disposal Policy|publisher=Tyne & Wear Archives & Museums|date=22 November 2012|accessdate=15 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[1973 Tyne and Wear County Council election]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Former county councils of England}}\n\n[[Category:Former county councils of England]]\n[[Category:History of Tyne and Wear]]\n[[Category:1974 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:1986 disestablishments in England]]\n[[Category:Tyne and Wear|County Council]]\n\n{{politics-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:stub sorting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tyne_and_Wear_County_Council"}
{"title_page": "Garuda Bairiya", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the table at Infobox settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  -->\n|name                   = Garuda Bairiya\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            = \u0917\u0930\u0941\u0921\u093e \u092c\u0948\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e\n|nickname               = Garuda\n|settlement_type        = [[Village development committee (Nepal)|Village development committee]]\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  -->\n|image_skyline          =\n|image_caption          =\n|image_flag             =\n|image_seal             =\n|image_map              = <!-- NepalRautahatDistrictmap.png -->\n|mapsize                = 300px\n|map_caption            = Map of the village development committees in Rautahat District\n|pushpin_map            = Nepal\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 300\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in Nepal\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = {{flag|Nepal}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Zones of Nepal|Zone]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Narayani Zone]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Districts of Nepal|District]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Rautahat District]]\n|<!-- Politics -->\n|government_footnotes   =\n|government_type        =\n|leader_title           =\n|leader_name            =\n|leader_title1          = <!-- for places with, say, both a mayor and a city manager -->\n|leader_name1           =\n|established_title      = <!-- Settled -->\n|established_date       =\n<!-- Area    -->\n|unit_pref                =  <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           = <!-- ALL fields dealing with a measurements are subject to automatic unit conversion-->\n<!-- Population   -->\n|population_as_of               = 1991\n|population_footnotes           =\n|population_note                =\n|population_total               = 1878\n|population_density_km2         = auto\n|population_blank1_title        = Ethnicities\n<!-- General information  -->\n|timezone               = [[Nepal Time]]\n|utc_offset             = +5:45\n|timezone_DST           =\n|utc_offset_DST         =\n|coordinates            = {{coord|26.95|85.32|type:adm2nd_region:NP_source:unmaps-enwiki|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    = <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m            =\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              =\n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|website                =\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Garuda Bairiya ''' is a [[Village development committee (Nepal)|village development committee]] in [[Rautahat District]] in the [[Narayani Zone]] of south-eastern [[Nepal]]. At the time of the [[1991 Nepal census]] it had a population of 1878 people living in 313 individual households. By 2012, the VDC had largely increased in size and its population reached more than 10000 approximately. The village is divided into two areas: the bajar and the gaun. Birendra highway passes through the Bajar which has Chandranigahpur on the north connecting the East-West highway and Gaur on the south which is on the Nepal-India Border. The VDC gained its fortune after the Birendra Highway was constructed. After the highway construction, developments and infrastructures followed around the VDC areas. In ancient time, the owner of Garuda gaun is Mathur Chaudhry In 1994 A.D. Shree Ram Sugar Mill was erected in Garuda. With the establishment of the sugar industry, farmers had opportunity to open business with the factory. They increased their sugarcane farming and sold it to the factory in their backyard. The factory provided jobs and opened sources of business in the VDC.  Hence, today the VDC is a fast-growing town with every business one can name. It is the center of business in the area with few banks, five-six petrol pumps, hundreds of Grocery stores, handful of Shopping centers, small granary and Eating-oil mills, shoes factory, a High school, several restaurants, clinics and Elaka police Station. It has highest economic rate among all villages in its districts. Some of the major castes like Jaiswal,Sharma,etc are well known for their business standard in Garuda. The VDC also has a movie theatre.  Transport is available throughout all day and sparsely at the night. Approximately 50% of the people are involved directly in farming and the other 50% in Business or other traditional works.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/nepalcensus/form.php?selection=1|title=Nepal Census 2001|work=Nepal's Village Development Committees|publisher=[[Digital Himalaya]]|accessdate=25 November 2008 }}</ref>\n\n== Media ==\nTo promote local culture Garuda has one FM radio station, Radio Madhesh Jana awaj{{Snd}} 98.6&nbsp;MHz, which is a [[community radio]] station.\n\nTo promote local culture Garuda has one FM radio station, radio madhesh masla{{Snd}} 106.4&nbsp;MHz, which is a [[community radio]] station.\n\n== Hospital ==\n\n# '''Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/Prakashjit+eye+care+&+Opticals/@26.9502831,85.316573,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x39ec9995cb495343:0xe67724eaa963911f!8m2!3d26.9502783!4d85.3187617|title=Prakashjit eye care & Opticals|website=Prakashjit eye care & Opticals|language=en|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref>\n\nPrakashjit eye care & opticals is the first eye care center in [[Garuda Municipality|Garuda]] Municipality, Rautahat district, Nepal. Ram prakash shah is the Chairman/founder of Prakashjit foundation, Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://prakashjitfoundati.wixsite.com/prakashjit/meet-the-team|title=Meet the Team {{!}} Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals Clinic|website=Foundation {{!}} https://prakashjitfoundati.wixsite.com/prakashjit {{!}} Nepal|language=en|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref> Dr. Sanjay Kumar Shah is the Managing Director of Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/people/Sanjay-Kumar/100000989066730|title=Sanjay Kumar|website=facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref> He has done various n'''ational''' as well as '''international''' work in the field of eye care & vision. He served people of Kenya as a senior optometrist/branch manager at '''OPTICA''', NAIROBI, KENYA.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://optica.africa/|title=Optica's Online Store {{!}} Frames, Sunglasses, Contact Lenses, and More.|website=Optica's Online Store|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref> He also worked as clinical optometrist at '''Dr. Om Parkash Eye Institute''', Amritsar, India<ref name=\":0\" /> & at '''LAWRENCE & MAYO (INDIA) PVT. LTD., Mumbai, India.'''\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Rautahat District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Rautahat District]]\n\n\n{{Province2NP-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the table at Infobox settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  -->\n|name                   = Garuda Bairiya\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            = \u0917\u0930\u0941\u0921\u093e \u092c\u0948\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e\n|nickname               = Garuda\n|settlement_type        = [[Village development committee (Nepal)|Village development committee]]\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  -->\n|image_skyline          =\n|image_caption          =\n|image_flag             =\n|image_seal             =\n|image_map              = <!-- NepalRautahatDistrictmap.png -->\n|mapsize                = 300px\n|map_caption            = Map of the village development committees in Rautahat District\n|pushpin_map            = Nepal\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 300\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in Nepal\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = {{flag|Nepal}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Zones of Nepal|Zone]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Narayani Zone]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Districts of Nepal|District]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Rautahat District]]\n|<!-- Politics -->\n|government_footnotes   =\n|government_type        =\n|leader_title           =\n|leader_name            =\n|leader_title1          = <!-- for places with, say, both a mayor and a city manager -->\n|leader_name1           =\n|established_title      = <!-- Settled -->\n|established_date       =\n<!-- Area    -->\n|unit_pref                =  <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           = <!-- ALL fields dealing with a measurements are subject to automatic unit conversion-->\n<!-- Population   -->\n|population_as_of               = 1991\n|population_footnotes           =\n|population_note                =\n|population_total               = 1878\n|population_density_km2         = auto\n|population_blank1_title        = Ethnicities\n<!-- General information  -->\n|timezone               = [[Nepal Time]]\n|utc_offset             = +5:45\n|timezone_DST           =\n|utc_offset_DST         =\n|coordinates            = {{coord|26.95|85.32|type:adm2nd_region:NP_source:unmaps-enwiki|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    = <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m            =\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              =\n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|website                =\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Garuda Bairiya ''' is a [[Village development committee (Nepal)|village development committee]] in [[Rautahat District]] in the [[Narayani Zone]] of south-eastern [[Nepal]]. At the time of the [[1991 Nepal census]] it had a population of 1878 people living in 313 individual households. By 2012, the VDC had largely increased in size and its population reached more than 10000 approximately. The village is divided into two areas: the bajar and the gaun. Birendra highway passes through the Bajar which has Chandranigahpur on the north connecting the East-West highway and Gaur on the south which is on the Nepal-India Border. The VDC gained its fortune after the Birendra Highway was constructed. After the highway construction, developments and infrastructures followed around the VDC areas. In ancient time, the owner of Garuda gaun is Mathur Chaudhry In 1994 A.D. Shree Ram Sugar Mill was erected in Garuda. With the establishment of the sugar industry, farmers had opportunity to open business with the factory. They increased their sugarcane farming and sold it to the factory in their backyard. The factory provided jobs and opened sources of business in the VDC.  Hence, today the VDC is a fast-growing town with every business one can name. It is the center of business in the area with few banks, five-six petrol pumps, hundreds of Grocery stores, handful of Shopping centers, small granary and Eating-oil mills, shoes factory, a High school, several restaurants, clinics and Elaka police Station. It has highest economic rate among all villages in its districts. Some of the major castes like Jaiswal,Sharma,etc are well known for their business standard in Garuda. The VDC also has a movie theatre.  Transport is available throughout all day and sparsely at the night. Approximately 50% of the people are involved directly in farming and the other 50% in Business or other traditional works.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/nepalcensus/form.php?selection=1|title=Nepal Census 2001|work=Nepal's Village Development Committees|publisher=[[Digital Himalaya]]|accessdate=25 November 2008 }}</ref>\n\n== Media ==\nTo promote local culture Garuda has one FM radio station, Radio Madhesh Jana awaj{{Snd}} 98.6&nbsp;MHz, which is a [[community radio]] station.\n\nTo promote local culture Garuda has one FM radio station, radio madhesh masla{{Snd}} 106.4&nbsp;MHz, which is a [[community radio]] station.\n\n== Hospital ==\n\n# '''Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/Prakashjit+eye+care+&+Opticals/@26.9502831,85.316573,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x39ec9995cb495343:0xe67724eaa963911f!8m2!3d26.9502783!4d85.3187617|title=Prakashjit eye care & Opticals|website=Prakashjit eye care & Opticals|language=en|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref>\n\nPrakashjit eye care & opticals is the first eye care center in [[Garuda Municipality|Garuda]] Municipality, Rautahat district, Nepal. Ram prakash shah is the Chairman/founder of Prakashjit foundation, Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://prakashjitfoundati.wixsite.com/prakashjit/meet-the-team|title=Meet the Team {{!}} Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals Clinic|website=Foundation {{!}} https://prakashjitfoundati.wixsite.com/prakashjit {{!}} Nepal|language=en|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref> Dr. Sanjay Kumar Shah is the Managing Director of Prakashjit Eye Care & Opticals,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/people/Sanjay-Kumar/100000989066730|title=Sanjay Kumar|website=facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref> He has done various n'''ational''' as well as '''international''' work in the field of eye care & vision. He served people of Kenya as a senior optometrist/branch manager at '''OPTICA''', NAIROBI, KENYA.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://optica.africa/|title=Optica's Online Store {{!}} Frames, Sunglasses, Contact Lenses, and More.|website=Optica's Online Store|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref> He also worked as clinical optometrist at '''Dr. Om Parkash Eye Institute''', Amritsar, India<ref name=\":0\" /> & at '''LAWRENCE & MAYO (INDIA) PVT. LTD., Mumbai, India.'''\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Rautahat District}}\n